parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The dash lights and gauges malfunction
the engine stalls or shuts down
the vehicle loses power
the accelerator fails
and the vehicle may restart on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of accidents by reducing the visibility of the vehicle to other drivers.
symptoms: The rear brake lights are inoperable

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause the vehicle to shut down while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while in motion
the engine stalls
the lights and radio remain on
the vehicle will not rev or respond to throttle input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan motor can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: A burning odor is present inside the vehicle
smoke is visible from the engine compartment
the cooling fan motor fails internally.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaks and Crankshaft End Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft end seal can cause engine oil to leak onto the road, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine oil light flashes
the oil level is low
oil is leaking from the accessories end of the engine
the crankshaft end seal is expelled from the timing cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage and failure, causing a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle uses excessive amounts of oil
the oil level is low
the engine oil light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. Leaks in the power steering system can lead to a loss of power assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle.
symptoms: Power steering fluid leaks
difficulty steering
loss of power assist
steering wheel vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle shuts down or stalls while driving
gauges malfunction
weird sounds
loss of power
difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering column failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. A loose or faulty steering column can lead to a loss of steering ability, making it difficult to control the vehicle.
symptoms: Vibration in the steering wheel
loose steering wheel
difficulty steering
whole steering column needs to be replaced.
